1
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,440
When you didn't want to,
you just ghosted me.

2
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,480
Do you have any idea how I would feel?

3
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:32,880
Only a lunatic like you
would reject Ms. Natedao.

4
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,600
She is too good for me.

5
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:37,320
I don't want to pull her down to my level.

6
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,200
PREVIOUSLY

7
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,920
That is for my friend.

8
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,200
I came here today

9
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,600
because I'll be at a piano contest

10
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:49,720
and I want emotional support
from you the most.

11
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,840
Whether you come to support me,

12
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,320
it's your call.

13
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,200
So who did this to you?

14
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,760
Petch.

15
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,560
You're dead meat.

16
00:03:58,640 --> 00:04:01,160
You folded paper stars
for Natedao, didn't you?

17
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,760
Hello, ma'am, sir.

18
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:12,400
Hello, Ake.

19
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:17,360
You're here earlier than the competitor.
Are you excited for Dao?

20
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:23,000
If I could compete for her,
I would, ma'am.

21
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,880
Very thoughtful.

22
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,080
I'll go ahead and get ready.

23
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,080
She must be feeling down from last night.

24
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,560
Don't overthink it.

25
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,000
Yes, sir.

26
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,880
I always understand her.

27
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:07,840
Hurry up, Petch!
You'll miss the competition.

28
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,240
Thanks, Dam.

29
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:13,040
By the way, I have a favor to ask.

30
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,680
- What is it?
- Here.

31
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,920
This month's payment and my commission

32
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,880
amount to 30,000 baht.

33
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:28,480
Wow, Petch, you're amazing.

34
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,320
Now, you can pay Mr. Nop's debt.

35
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,960
I want you to take that money to my dad.

36
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,920
Why?

37
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:39,240
If I do it myself, he will question it.

38
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,480
Make something up and take it to him.

39
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,360
- Appreciate it, man.
- Petch.

40
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,800
What a devoted son. I'm so proud of you.

41
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:48,000
I don't need compliments. Enough.
I'm leaving now.

42
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,800
Good luck then.

43
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,360
Go.

44
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,760
Make something up.

45
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,920
"Mr. Nop, here."

46
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:00,080
"Petch got this money from…"

47
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,640
A donation drive?

48
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,280
No, that doesn't sound right.

49
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,280
Where is he?

50
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,120
Dao.

51
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,320
Who are you looking for?

52
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,520
Oh, no one.

53
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:28,920
The competition is starting soon.

54
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:30,640
Right.

55
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:32,360
We're here to cheer for you.

56
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:35,040
You can win this.

57
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:37,360
Thank you.

58
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:40,040
We're looking forward to the good news.

59
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,840
I think you should go prepare inside.

60
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:44,680
The emcee will call you soon.

61
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:47,240
- Come on.
- Let's go.

62
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,880
Come with us.

63
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:01,040
Hello, Nop.

64
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,720
Venerable Father.

65
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:07,600
I will go back to work tomorrow
as a taxi driver.

66
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:10,240
I came here to tell you

67
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:14,120
before I start anew for luck.

68
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,280
Nop, are you fully recovered?

69
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,280
I think I'm getting well.

70
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,800
If I don't get back to work sooner,

71
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,720
I won't have money for Petch's school.

72
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,680
Is Petch quitting his job?

73
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,680
What do you mean?

74
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,960
Petch works at an auto garage.

75
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,480
Didn't you know?

76
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,280
I didn't know.

77
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,360
Venerable Father.

78
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,880
Do you perhaps know where Petch works?

79
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,080
Where is it located?

80
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,080
Shoot.

81
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,800
The paper stars.

82
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:58,040
Petch, you dummy.

83
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,760
Petch!

84
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,800
Hello? What's up, Dam?

85
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:17,360
You forgot the paper stars here.

86
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:20,680
You're right.

87
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,840
I left it there.

88
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,680
Thanks. I'm heading back to get it.

89
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,080
How did I forget?

90
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,960
Hello, buddy.

91
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,560
Do you recognize me?

92
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,680
I never had buddies like you.

93
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,440
You're only the protagonist's buddy then?

94
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,200
You know what?

95
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,880
The protagonist's buddy
always dies in the end.

96
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,840
Dam!

97
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,920
Dam! Are you all right?

98
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,840
Dam!

99
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,640
Dam!

100
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,000
Petch.

101
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,360
You need to leave for the show.

102
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,800
How can I leave you?

103
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:52,440
Stop talking, Petch.

104
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,160
I will make you pay.

105
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:56,440
Pay for what?

106
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,200
You dare ask me that?

107
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,960
Who the heck hit me in the head?

108
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,800
It wasn't Petch.

109
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,880
It was me who hit you.

110
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,960
Dam!

111
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,960
This moron Joe

112
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,120
got you expelled, didn't he?

113
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,600
He got you expelled!

114
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:19,960
You fools!

115
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,800
That wouldn't have happened to him

116
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:25,240
if he hadn't dared to flirt with Dao.

117
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:26,480
What do you mean?

118
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,080
Why is it about Dao?

119
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,080
You are beyond dumb.

120
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,000
Out of all people,

121
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,760
you chose to like

122
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,440
Akekaphol's girl.

123
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,160
What do you mean?

124
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:44,080
Akekaphol is pissed that you like Dao,
so he hired me to get you expelled.

125
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,960
I'm curious.

126
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,600
Is Dao…

127
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,040
that good?

128
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,720
Shut your dirty mouth.

129
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:24,040
You have no right to talk about her.

130
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,920
Listen to him, guys.

131
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,160
The hero is protecting the heroine

132
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,360
both in front of her

133
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,760
and behind her!

134
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,480
How often do you get lucky

135
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,040
to be this protective?

136
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,280
Remember this, Joe.

137
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,200
A man should never

138
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,080
look down on women.

139
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,800
Petch! Look out!

140
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:32,240
Joe.

141
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,240
Your blood…

142
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:39,200
It was an accident, Joe.

143
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,200
Joe!

144
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,800
- Blood.
- Damn you, Petch!

145
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,840
- It was an accident.
- Joe!

146
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,720
- Joe!
- Joe!

147
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,880
- Joe!
- Joe!

148
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,760
- So much blood.
- Joe.

149
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,640
- Dam.
- Petch!

150
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,400
- You killed Joe!
- Murderer!

151
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,040
You killed Joe!

152
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:03,480
- I killed Joe!
- Joe!

153
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:06,200
- Joe!
- No!

154
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:09,520
- Joe!
- Joe! It was an accident!

155
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,280
I didn't do it on purpose! Joe!

156
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,760
He sneaks into work at an auto garage

157
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:53,360
and doesn't pick up the phone.

158
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,360
Why is it so crowded here?

159
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,640
What's going on, sir?

160
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,800
Oh, there's a murder scene.

161
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,080
What murder?

162
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,120
The murderer is over there!

163
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,080
Go.

164
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:37,680
- Dad.
- Petch!

165
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,120
Dad!

166
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,160
Petch!

167
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:42,240
- Don't come in.
- He's my son!

168
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,440
Let go of me!

169
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:44,640
- Mr. Nop, calm down!
- Dad!

170
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,600
- What's going on?
- Mr. Nop, calm down!

171
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,480
- What is this? Petch!
- You can't come in.

172
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:50,080
- Mr. Nop, calm down!
- What's happening?

173
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:53,000
- Mr. Nop, calm down!
- He is my son!

174
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:53,960
Mr. Nop, calm down!

175
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,520
- What is going on?
- Dad!

176
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:58,280
- Petch killed a man.
- Get in.

177
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,760
He killed a man.

178
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:03,120
Why is he being arrested?
What has he done?

179
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,400
Mr. Nop, please stay calm.

180
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:07,080
What did he do? Say it!

181
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:11,720
Petch killed a man.

182
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:15,000
Petch murdered a man.

183
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:20,920
Petch!

184
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:41,440
Look at that.

185
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:47,200
Dao just let someone else win.

186
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:50,520
She didn't get any award.

187
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:55,120
I have never been this upset.

188
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:58,600
I'm very disappointed in her.

189
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,320
Dao.

190
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:07,520
I'm not good enough.

191
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,079
I'm such a failure.

192
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:15,359
I'm sorry for failing you both.

193
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,319
- Dao, dear.
- Dao.

194
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,599
Dao.

195
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,240
Don't worry, ma'am. Let me talk to her.

196
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:23,440
Dao.

197
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,319
Dao.

198
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:31,920
Dao.

199
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,240
Dao.

200
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,560
Dao, watch out!

201
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,600
- Dao!
- Dao.

202
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:42,840
Dao.

203
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,840
- Dao.
- Oh, no.

204
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,200
Dao.

205
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,320
Are you okay, dear?

206
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,360
I'm okay.

207
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:52,480
Oh, dear.

208
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,720
It's a relief that she isn't hurt.

209
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,760
Akekaphol, dear, you're bleeding.

210
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:04,080
He's hurt from protecting her.

211
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:08,280
Akekaphol, let's go to the hospital
and have it checked.

212
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,080
All right, sir.

213
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:11,440
Let's go, honey.

214
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:18,280
Petch!

215
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:21,280
Don't say anything.

216
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:23,840
I'll hire a lawyer for you.

217
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,400
Your son admitted to the crime.

218
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:34,960
Petch.

219
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:37,760
But it was an accident, sir.

220
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,640
Joe started the fight!

221
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:44,240
The evidence and witnesses
are against him.

222
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:48,160
Moreover, he admitted himself
that he killed Joe.

223
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:52,600
- Officer! Did you make my son admit?
- Dad!

224
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,760
- Officer!
- Sir!

225
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:55,720
Calm down.

226
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,600
I'm in the wrong.

227
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,600
I killed Joe.

228
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,520
Petch!

229
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:13,360
Are you lying to me?

230
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:18,320
You told me

231
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,160
you went to school every day.

232
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,200
But you worked

233
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:28,400
at that auto garage instead.

234
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,160
You're lying right now, aren't you?

235
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,000
You taught me

236
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:39,760
that a real man

237
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:41,600
owns up

238
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:43,480
to his responsibility.

239
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,680
I've committed a crime.

240
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,160
I should be punished for it.

241
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:55,640
Petch, are you out of your mind?

242
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:57,680
How long will you be in jail?

243
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,080
What about Mr. Nop and me?
Do you think about us?

244
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,520
Dam.

245
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,040
I know both of you are worried about me.

246
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,080
But I really can't

247
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,000
run away from my mess.

248
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:17,800
Don't cry, Dad.

249
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:21,080
Let's just say
you never had a son like me.

250
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:26,240
Petch.

251
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,880
Have you lost your mind?

252
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,000
I've raised you to this day.

253
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,640
How could I even think that?

254
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,760
Petch.

255
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:53,800
Petch.

256
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,440
Son.

257
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:59,840
How could I forget about you?

258
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:03,600
All right.

259
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:06,320
I have to proceed further now.

260
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:09,280
Petch.

261
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,280
This way, please.

262
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:12,200
Petch.

263
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,440
Petch.

264
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,240
Petch.

265
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:24,720
- Mr. Nop.
- Petch. My son.

266
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:26,760
Petch.

267
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,600
- Officer!
- You can't go in, sir.

268
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,960
Officer! Take me instead, please.

269
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,040
Petch.

270
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:35,360
Officer! Don't take my son, sir.

271
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:38,440
Please take me instead.

272
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:40,360
Mr. Nop. Petch.

273
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:41,600
Petch.

274
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,040
Petch!

275
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:45,160
Petch!

276
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:47,040
Hang in there, my son.

277
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,960
I'll find a way to get you out.

278
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:53,640
Petch!

279
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,040
Petch!

280
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,400
Petch!

281
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,960
Hang in there.

282
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:39,120
Santi, Penyapa.

283
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:41,200
- Hello.
- Sompob.

284
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:44,280
I hurried here as soon as I heard.

285
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:47,000
How is Akekaphol doing?

286
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:49,920
The doctor is checking up on him now.
They should be out soon.

287
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:53,520
I have to apologize to you.

288
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:57,440
He's hurt because of Dao.

289
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:59,760
Don't blame it on her.

290
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:02,360
Who would want this to happen?

291
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:07,840
Oh, Akekaphol is here.

292
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,200
- Akekaphol.
- Akekaphol.

293
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,280
Please don't worry.

294
00:23:11,800 --> 00:23:14,240
It's only a four-stitch wound.
Not a big deal.

295
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:17,080
I appreciate your action.

296
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:20,680
If it wasn't for you,
Dao would have been hit by that motorbike.

297
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,760
Sir, please don't thank me.

298
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,000
For Dao,

299
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:27,760
this is nothing.

300
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,080
I would give her my life.

301
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:35,840
Dear, why are you just standing here?

302
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,320
Say thank you to Akekaphol.

303
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:40,000
Hey, Dao.

304
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:42,760
You're burning up!

305
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:44,760
Does she have a fever?

306
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:46,480
- Dao! Dao, dear.
- Dao.

307
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:48,440
Dao.

308
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:50,520
She's burning up.

309
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,600
Honey.

310
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:09,840
Akekaphol, sir. Aren't you injured?

311
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,360
My arm is, but not my throat.

312
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,240
By the way, Mud,

313
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:21,280
when something bad happens,

314
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,560
it comes with an opportunity.

315
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,040
What are you talking about, sir?

316
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:30,760
Little blood I bleed,

317
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:35,480
I have won over my future in-laws already.

318
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:37,840
Congratulations, sir.

319
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:41,080
Dao can get married
as soon as she graduates.

320
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:44,280
Married, my butt.

321
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:48,240
I saved her life
and she didn't care one bit.

322
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:50,280
It pisses me off.

323
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:55,400
Is it because Dao is not over Petch?

324
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,280
Mud.

325
00:24:58,080 --> 00:24:59,480
Why are you mentioning him?

326
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,680
You know that I hate him.

327
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:04,000
I'm sorry, sir.

328
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:07,360
That damn Petch

329
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,760
got expelled
in the middle of the semester.

330
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:12,760
Isn't it over for him?

331
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,760
Dao wouldn't be that dumb

332
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,720
to date a failure like him.

333
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,400
BOONYAVEJ HOSPITAL, NATEDAO AKKARANGKUL

334
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:34,480
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

335
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:40,800
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

336
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:47,400
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

337
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:52,600
<i>But never reaching you</i>

338
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:56,160
Petch.

339
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:58,920
I'm here to visit.

340
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:01,120
Get well soon.

341
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:04,640
I'm not dreaming, am I?

342
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:22,360
Don't cry.

343
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:24,840
Let's sing.

344
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:32,080
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

345
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:38,000
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

346
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:44,960
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

347
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:50,600
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

348
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:56,440
<i>You are out of reach</i>

349
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:57,520
Damn you, Petch!

350
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,240
Petch.

351
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,120
Hello.

352
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:26,240
Petch.

353
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:28,520
I thought you wouldn't pick up my call.

354
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:31,680
Well…

355
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:35,520
It's not him speaking. It's me, Damrong.

356
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:36,960
Oh, I see.

357
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:38,640
Where is Petch, then?

358
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:39,800
Dao.

359
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:43,800
Listen carefully.

360
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:46,160
<i>He doesn't want anything to do with you.</i>

361
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:48,960
Why?

362
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:50,840
It's because…

363
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:53,160
You're too good for him.
Please leave him alone.

364
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:56,040
I'm too good for him,

365
00:27:57,280 --> 00:28:00,000
so he didn't show up
at my piano competition?

366
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:04,000
Whatever the reason, just keep in mind

367
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:05,520
that you are not meant to be.

368
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:09,160
Don't call this number anymore.
He's canceling this number.

369
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:34,240
What did you say, dear?

370
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:37,200
You want to study in the US?

371
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:39,400
That's odd, dear.

372
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:42,320
You said you weren't going
and prefer to stay here.

373
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:43,960
I changed my mind.

374
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:47,040
Don't you both want me to go?

375
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:52,440
Hello.

376
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,160
- Hello.
- Dao.

377
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:55,720
I came to visit.

378
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,120
- Akekaphol, come here.
- Ma'am?

379
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:00,200
Please talk to her.

380
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:03,320
She changed her mind and wants
to study abroad all of a sudden.

381
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,200
Dao.

382
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:06,680
Are you serious?

383
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:07,720
Yes.

384
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:12,080
I think that the sooner I go abroad,

385
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,200
the sooner I'll learn the language.

386
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:17,640
I hope you agree. It is for my future.

387
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:20,280
Dao, you said it frankly.

388
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:22,160
How could I disagree?

389
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:24,960
It's settled then.

390
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:29,840
I promise to keep my grades up.

391
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,840
The court determines

392
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:45,560
that the defendant is guilty
of an offense under Section 290,

393
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:48,440
first paragraph, of the Criminal Code,

394
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,640
for causing the death of another person

395
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:54,400
by an act of violence
without the intent to kill.

396
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:58,880
At the time the offense was committed,
the defendant was 17 years of age.

397
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:02,360
The court reduces the scale of punishment
by half in accordance

398
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:06,160
with Criminal Code Section 75,
imprisonment of 4 years.

399
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,680
The defendant's confession,

400
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:12,200
being beneficial to the trial,
provides grounds for mitigation.

401
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:17,120
<i>The punishment shall be reduced</i>
<i>by half according to Section 78</i>

402
00:30:17,200 --> 00:30:19,320
<i>of the Criminal Code.</i>

403
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:22,960
<i>Based on the observation center's report,</i>

404
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:25,240
<i>the court finds</i>

405
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:28,720
<i>that the defendant acted</i>
<i>out of youthful impulsivity</i>

406
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:31,800
<i>and lack of due deliberation.</i>

407
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:36,040
<i>For the purpose of rehabilitation</i>
<i>and character reform,</i>

408
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:40,080
<i>which would be more beneficial</i>
<i>than imprisonment,</i>

409
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:44,440
<i>the Juvenile and Family Court</i>

410
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:50,320
<i>and Procedure Act BE 2553,</i>

411
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:53,600
<i>Section 142, Semi Section 1,</i>

412
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:57,520
<i>hereby reduces the term of imprisonment.</i>

413
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:58,960
<i>The defendant shall be detained</i>

414
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:01,040
<i>for training</i>
<i>at the Juvenile Training Center,</i>

415
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:03,880
<i>effective from the date of this judgment.</i>

416
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:05,680
<i>The seized knife is hereby forfeited.</i>

417
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:15,480
KANCHANAPHISEK HOUSE

418
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:19,400
Welcome to everyone who came in today.

419
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:23,880
First, I would like to inform you

420
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,600
that this is not a child jail.

421
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:28,920
None of you are prisoners.

422
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:32,760
This is a temporary home

423
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:36,360
for teenagers who made mistakes.

424
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:41,480
Everyone has a chance
to reform themselves.

425
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:47,000
Therefore, everyone here
will get a chance to study

426
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,560
and sharpen their skills

427
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:51,360
according to their liking

428
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,520
to prepare themselves

429
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:57,520
for their new life in society.

430
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:10,880
Focus on your studies, my dear.

431
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,400
Yes, Mom.

432
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,320
Okay.

433
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:15,880
Let's go, Dao.

434
00:32:21,960 --> 00:32:22,960
Please excuse us.

435
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:32,280
I believe everyone
has a future career in mind.

436
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,800
Please write down what your dream is.

437
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:37,680
Don't worry about failing.

438
00:32:37,760 --> 00:32:39,520
Write them down first.

439
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:41,920
We'll share it with the class later.

440
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:54,520
Why aren't you writing it down, Petch?

441
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:57,160
My dreams have died, ma'am.

442
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,880
I don't know what to write.

443
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:01,240
I'm sorry, ma'am.

444
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:07,800
JUVENILE TRAINING CENTER

445
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,680
Let's go.

446
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:13,600
- He is stalling.
- Right.

447
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,480
Is he new?

448
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:19,200
Yes. Let's get him.

449
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:21,880
Let's see.

450
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:24,920
Hey, new boy.

451
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:27,560
What are you here for?

452
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,120
Berm is asking. Why don't you answer?

453
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,560
His name is Petch.

454
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:35,760
He is here for murder.

455
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:37,760
Look at his face.

456
00:33:38,360 --> 00:33:40,920
He wants to fight. Let's fight him.

457
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,320
Are you asking for a fight?

458
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:52,560
Damn.

459
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:57,040
You asked for it when you ignored Berm.

460
00:33:57,120 --> 00:33:58,600
You messed with the wrong guy.

461
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,240
Remember this.

462
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:03,200
I don't care how tough you are.

463
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:04,280
Right here,

464
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,240
I've taken over.

465
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:07,560
Keep that in mind.

466
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,560
Let's go.

467
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:13,080
His face pisses me off.

468
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:15,360
Let's fight him one more round.

469
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,200
Stay still!

470
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:03,320
What are you doing?

471
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:04,520
Washing clothes?

472
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:06,520
I'm just messing with you.

473
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,800
You are quite funny.

474
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,240
Right.

475
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:14,880
Stand still. I'm drawing you.

476
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:20,440
I'm Piak. What's your name?

477
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:21,920
Petch.

478
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:25,000
Petch, come look at this.

479
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:29,160
Hey.

480
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,560
- Hey.
- Yes?

481
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:35,760
Your drawing is incredible.

482
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:37,800
I'm the best here.

483
00:35:37,880 --> 00:35:39,600
You're trapped here

484
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,840
and you still have the heart to draw?

485
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,640
It is true that we're trapped here.

486
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:50,320
But no one can trap our dreams.

487
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:00,080
Piak. Where are you going?

488
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,120
Hey.

489
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:08,280
Did you draw all these?

490
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,760
Yes, I drew all of these.

491
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,920
These are my dreams.

492
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:14,440
Oh, wow.

493
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:15,520
What the hell is going on here?

494
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:18,120
ART EXHIBITION

495
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:24,360
Who said you can place ugly drawings here?

496
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:33,120
Guys.

497
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,000
Get rid of them.

498
00:36:35,080 --> 00:36:36,120
Let's go, brother.

499
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:44,480
Done, brother.

500
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:45,880
Next time,

501
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:47,400
if you want a model,

502
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:53,000
you can draw my ingrown toenail.

503
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:09,440
I don't care if you look down on me.

504
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:12,840
But you don't have the right
to look down on others' dreams.

505
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:14,120
Dream?

506
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,320
Take this.

507
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:19,480
Remember this.

508
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:21,840
In here,

509
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:23,880
you don't need dreams.

510
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:27,440
- Here.
- Hey.

511
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:29,800
- More!
- The teacher is here.

512
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:36,880
Are you new here?

513
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,960
If you need help, let me know.

514
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:46,840
Please excuse me.

515
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:48,640
- Goodbye, ma'am.
- Hold on.

516
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:53,960
What happened to the board?
Why is it messed up?

517
00:37:59,560 --> 00:38:02,240
Piak. They are your drawings.

518
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,000
Answer me.

519
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:05,120
What happened?

520
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:06,560
It…

521
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:12,480
I tore them, ma'am.
Every piece. I tore them myself.

522
00:38:13,080 --> 00:38:15,720
That is not true, ma'am.
Berm destroyed them.

523
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,720
He wanted to pick on Piak.

524
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:20,240
That seems like it.

525
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:23,000
Piak has no reason
to tear down his own work.

526
00:38:26,600 --> 00:38:28,680
We need to talk about this.

527
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:31,640
Berm, Chai, Sert.

528
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:34,240
You three, follow me.

529
00:38:45,280 --> 00:38:46,320
I'll get you later.

530
00:38:58,160 --> 00:38:59,000
Petch.

531
00:39:00,560 --> 00:39:02,400
Thank you for standing up for me.

532
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:03,320
It's nothing.

533
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:05,280
That's not true. It's a big deal.

534
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:07,520
You are targeted because of it.

535
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,840
What are you scared of?

536
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:11,000
We did nothing wrong, Piak.

537
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:12,920
Everyone here is scared of Berm.

538
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:14,800
That's why he thinks so highly of himself.

539
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:16,760
That's why he picks on you.

540
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:19,960
Come to think of it,

541
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:23,680
you're a little too cowardly to be here.

542
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:25,160
You're right.

543
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:28,200
I'm a coward. I'm scared.

544
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:30,160
People in the slum area forced me

545
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:32,400
to stand guard for them
while housebreaking.

546
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:35,080
The house owner came back that day.

547
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,000
They killed him

548
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:39,120
and I got arrested too.

549
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:40,640
Then I got sent here.

550
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:41,760
That's a shame.

551
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:44,080
You didn't do it on purpose.

552
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:47,240
But I was wrong anyway.
I feel sorry for my mom.

553
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,600
I made her cry.

554
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:51,360
I want to get out and see her.

555
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:56,080
I know how you feel, Piak.

556
00:39:58,440 --> 00:39:59,680
But what can we do?

557
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:01,520
It is

558
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,560
what it is.

559
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:06,240
Hey.

560
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:12,400
Remember.

561
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:13,520
This world

562
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:16,200
has no place for the weak.

563
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,360
Mr. Nop.

564
00:40:35,640 --> 00:40:36,760
What is it, Dam?

565
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:40,520
I've been busy lately,
so I wasn't able to give this to you.

566
00:40:40,600 --> 00:40:42,360
Petch asked me to give this to you.

567
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:47,440
Hey.

568
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:48,640
Thirty grand.

569
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:51,360
Petch worked really hard
at the auto garage,

570
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:53,320
so he could help pay off your debt.

571
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:57,080
Petch.

572
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:59,720
The reason he hid

573
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:02,280
being expelled from school

574
00:41:02,880 --> 00:41:05,200
was that he didn't want to let you down.

575
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:07,680
Please forgive him.

576
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:09,680
I never resented him in the first place.

577
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,640
If I must resent anyone,

578
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:15,520
it should be me.

579
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:20,280
I barely know my own son.

580
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:32,440
LONG LIVE THE KING

581
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:44,960
Is this your dream?

582
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:50,880
Yes. How did you know?

583
00:41:50,960 --> 00:41:53,840
I saw you listening to music
the other day,

584
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:56,880
so I assumed you were into music.

585
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:57,880
That's right.

586
00:41:58,640 --> 00:41:59,960
Especially this.

587
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:02,120
Play it then.

588
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,240
Play something on your mind.

589
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:10,920
Your favorite track.

590
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:23,960
<i>It's strange</i>

591
00:43:24,480 --> 00:43:27,200
<i>how the song you played for me</i>

592
00:43:28,160 --> 00:43:30,520
<i>has changed my life.</i>

593
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:34,520
<i>From a person who didn't have any dreams,</i>

594
00:43:35,520 --> 00:43:40,320
<i>I got accepted to a music institute</i>
<i>while taking a business management course.</i>

595
00:43:41,720 --> 00:43:44,680
<i>Even though you refuse to see me again,</i>

596
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:47,280
<i>I still care for you.</i>

597
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:49,200
<i>I wish you happiness</i>

598
00:43:50,360 --> 00:43:51,920
<i>no matter where you are</i>

599
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:53,920
<i>or what you do.</i>

600
00:44:08,160 --> 00:44:11,360
Petch said he does not wish
to accept or see anyone.

601
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:13,760
Again?

602
00:44:13,840 --> 00:44:15,720
He always refuses every time we're here.

603
00:44:17,240 --> 00:44:18,480
Take his dad home.

604
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,240
And take this back.

605
00:44:24,920 --> 00:44:25,760
Mr. Nop.

606
00:44:26,440 --> 00:44:27,320
Mr. Nop.

607
00:44:28,120 --> 00:44:29,440
What about these?

608
00:44:30,040 --> 00:44:31,280
You take it, Dam.

609
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:34,400
Sir, I can't eat all this by myself.

610
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:35,920
Share it with the temple kids.

611
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:38,400
Let's say we're doing it for Petch.

612
00:44:40,360 --> 00:44:41,520
Oh, Petch.

613
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:43,880
He doesn't let us see him at all.

614
00:44:43,960 --> 00:44:45,160
This damn friend.

615
00:44:45,880 --> 00:44:47,280
You're his friend.

616
00:44:47,800 --> 00:44:49,520
Don't you know how he is?

617
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:53,360
You know how high his ego is.

618
00:44:53,440 --> 00:44:55,520
I know that well.

619
00:44:56,040 --> 00:44:59,840
I can't help but worry about
how he is doing inside these buildings.

620
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:01,840
Unless he is free and out,

621
00:45:02,360 --> 00:45:04,280
don't dream of even seeing
one of his hairs.

622
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:12,120
It's going to take years.

623
00:45:14,640 --> 00:45:15,680
What should I do?

624
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:26,320
I'm here for Bo.

625
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,280
What do you want?

626
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:36,520
Someone recommended me here.

627
00:45:37,040 --> 00:45:38,360
I heard you own this area.

628
00:45:39,520 --> 00:45:41,000
I'm short of money.

629
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:43,280
I want to work with you.

630
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:51,640
Here's your
informal education form, Petch.

631
00:45:52,160 --> 00:45:53,320
Fill it out, dear.

632
00:45:55,600 --> 00:45:56,680
Thank you, ma'am.

633
00:45:57,760 --> 00:45:59,040
Please save it for the others.

634
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:00,000
Why?

635
00:46:00,080 --> 00:46:01,840
I don't know why I should study.

636
00:46:02,520 --> 00:46:04,160
It's not going to change anything.

637
00:46:04,240 --> 00:46:05,120
Petch.

638
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:06,960
Listen to me carefully.

639
00:46:07,040 --> 00:46:10,160
A great man is not someone
who never messes up,

640
00:46:10,760 --> 00:46:13,640
but someone who fails
and tries to be better.

641
00:46:13,720 --> 00:46:15,960
You failed, but don't give up.

642
00:46:16,560 --> 00:46:17,680
Take it, dear.

643
00:46:17,760 --> 00:46:20,000
Sleep on it.

644
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:21,800
I'll wait for your answer.

645
00:46:31,560 --> 00:46:33,760
Just apply. It's a no-brainer.

646
00:46:35,280 --> 00:46:36,160
Did you apply?

647
00:46:36,240 --> 00:46:37,480
No, not yet.

648
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:39,040
See?

649
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:41,360
You agree with me.

650
00:46:42,160 --> 00:46:45,480
Whether we apply or not,
if other people reject us,

651
00:46:46,560 --> 00:46:47,480
it's pointless.

652
00:46:48,080 --> 00:46:49,680
Remember what you told me?

653
00:46:49,760 --> 00:46:51,760
This world has no place for the weak.

654
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:54,680
If we don't try, we won't stand a chance.

655
00:46:56,560 --> 00:46:59,360
Here. If you apply, I will apply too.

656
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:02,160
Where is he?

657
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:04,560
Who is applying for informal education?

658
00:47:07,680 --> 00:47:08,520
Give me that.

659
00:47:09,520 --> 00:47:10,600
Here you are, Berm.

660
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:16,280
You don't know your place, huh?

661
00:47:17,800 --> 00:47:18,880
What are you thinking?

662
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:21,200
Once you're out, you won't be back?

663
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:23,880
Right. Look at Berm here.

664
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:28,080
In and out three times, and here he is.

665
00:47:28,160 --> 00:47:29,520
He likes it here.

666
00:47:29,600 --> 00:47:31,240
He's been living here
longer than he had with his parents.

667
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:32,760
Right.

668
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:35,120
- Long?
- Yes, long.

669
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:36,920
You want to try me? I can be here longer.

670
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:39,720
I'll tell you something.

671
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:42,560
It won't change a thing if you apply.

672
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:47,560
Society already judges you for being here.

673
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:52,760
Keep that in mind.

674
00:47:52,840 --> 00:47:54,400
Hey. Don't pick on Petch!

675
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:57,280
Berm.

676
00:47:59,760 --> 00:48:00,720
Dam?

677
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:02,760
I'm glad to see you again, my friend.

678
00:48:03,280 --> 00:48:04,480
Dam, watch out!

679
00:48:06,720 --> 00:48:08,200
Hey!

680
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:11,800
Don't!

681
00:48:11,880 --> 00:48:14,640
Dam!

682
00:48:14,720 --> 00:48:15,560
Stop it!

683
00:48:15,640 --> 00:48:19,080
- What's going on?
- Back off!

684
00:48:19,160 --> 00:48:20,080
What's going on?

685
00:48:20,160 --> 00:48:22,280
- Arrest him, please!
- Stop!

686
00:48:22,360 --> 00:48:23,640
Don't point fingers.

687
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:27,240
The two of you fought.
The two of you will be punished.

688
00:48:28,040 --> 00:48:29,160
Who else is involved?

689
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:32,400
No one interfered, sir.

690
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:34,880
It was just me and this one.

691
00:48:36,280 --> 00:48:37,200
Bullshit.

692
00:48:37,280 --> 00:48:39,840
- Want more?
- Enough!

693
00:48:39,920 --> 00:48:40,760
That's enough.

694
00:48:41,560 --> 00:48:44,320
I'll double the punishment
if you don't stop.

695
00:48:45,240 --> 00:48:46,440
You too.

696
00:48:47,120 --> 00:48:48,760
If you're against the rules,

697
00:48:48,840 --> 00:48:50,760
you'll be punished by the rules.

698
00:48:51,280 --> 00:48:53,000
- Go.
- Go.

699
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:57,240
Come on.

700
00:49:24,280 --> 00:49:27,400
FIRST TIME ON THE BUS

701
00:49:36,560 --> 00:49:38,000
Can I keep the tickets?

702
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:40,560
Why?

703
00:49:41,440 --> 00:49:42,440
Just hand it to me.

704
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:13,160
No matter how long you try,
even if it is 10 years or 20 years,

705
00:50:13,720 --> 00:50:14,960
it's a waste of time.

706
00:50:15,560 --> 00:50:16,840
Let go, Akekaphol.

707
00:50:16,920 --> 00:50:18,680
NEXT EPISODE

708
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:21,440
Shoot!

709
00:50:21,520 --> 00:50:23,440
Somebody, please help!

710
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:25,840
Petch will be out soon.

711
00:50:27,040 --> 00:50:28,440
I'll take our son home.

712
00:50:28,520 --> 00:50:29,760
Thank you, ma'am.

713
00:50:30,560 --> 00:50:31,440
Thank you.

714
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:33,360
It has only been four or five years.

715
00:50:33,440 --> 00:50:36,000
You're all grown up.
I almost didn't recognize you.

716
00:50:36,080 --> 00:50:37,760
There's someone waiting for you.

717
00:50:51,760 --> 00:50:56,760
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

718
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:02,800
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

719
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:09,800
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

720
00:51:09,880 --> 00:51:14,520
<i>But never reaching you</i>

721
00:51:15,840 --> 00:51:20,440
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

722
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:26,720
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

723
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:33,600
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

724
00:51:34,320 --> 00:51:38,560
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

725
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:45,200
<i>You are out of reach</i>

726
00:51:45,960 --> 00:51:50,720
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

727
00:51:52,960 --> 00:51:57,760
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

728
00:51:57,840 --> 00:52:03,040
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

729
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:08,560
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

730
00:52:09,840 --> 00:52:15,000
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

731
00:52:15,880 --> 00:52:21,840
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

732
00:52:21,920 --> 00:52:27,760
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

733
00:52:27,840 --> 00:52:29,320
Subtitle translation by: Natnaree W.
